ion of the first edition. It includes expanded discussions of basic income, poverty reduction strategies, innovative housing polices, carbon pricing, and the role of health professionals in working for health equity, as well as new chapters on poverty, food security, and climate change. This book breaks important ground, showing us how a focus on health can change Canadian politics for the better.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHealthxPolitical aspectszCanada. 0aHealthxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aHealth-Political aspects-Canada. 0aHealth-Social aspects-Canada. 0aPublic healthxPolitical aspectszCanada. 0aPublic health-Political aspects-Canada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aPicard, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomanow, Hon. Roy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311141792940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077488027540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774880275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774880275/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-141792-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles